Telkom has published its annual report for the 2019 financial year, outlining the performance of the company and the salaries of its top executives. CEO Sipho Maseko earned a total of R23.2 million over the last financial year, comprising a guaranteed salary of R8.3 million, a bonus of R7 million, and a vested share payout of R5.3 million. Dividends paid on unvested shares totalled R2.56 million. Other highly-paid executives include chief financial officer (CFO) Deon Fredericks, who earned a total of R10.56 million, and his successor Tsholofelo Molefe, who earned a total of R7.8 million over the past year. Telkom paid its prescribed officers a total of R63.2 million for the year, which combined with director pay of R40.8 million, means the group paid a total of R104 million to its top executives. Below are the salaries earned by Telkom executive directors and prescribed officers, including CEO Sipho Maseko. The figures below include guaranteed pay (GP), short term incentives (STIs), long term incentives (LTIs), and total remuneration. Other contributors to total remuneration such as motor vehicle insurance and dividends paid on unvested shares were not included in the comparison. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-221555" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Telkom-office-mockup-logo.jpg" alt="Telkom office mockup logo" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Telkom-office-mockup-logo.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Telkom-office-mockup-logo-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Telkom-office-mockup-logo-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />